Summary: saw unusual cloud, but realized that it was more like a rocket's contrail
divs: Sighting DetailsDid not see the object that created this. I noticed it while driving that morning. It was a very tight vertical trail that ended in a cloudy plane. Lasted only 18-20 min before it dissipated. The skies were clear. I thought it might have been a cloud, or a smoke trail, but it was too thin and deliberate. There were spirals in the column, as if something was rotating while making the trail.
